    <item>
      <title>Howard University Volunteer Income Tax Assistance Program  at School of Business Building</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/51950813175058/huge/39feab064265dccb6f24fed0771e415e47737ecc.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Tue, 17 Mar 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>The Center for Accounting Education’s Volunteer Income Tax Assistance (VITA) Program provides free basic tax preparation services by IRS-trained volunteer tax preparers. Services are available to eligible Washington, DC–area residents and Howard University students.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Eligibility:
<br />Services are available to individuals who:</p>

<p>Earn $69,000 or less (low to moderate or fixed income)</p>

<p>Are elderly or disabled</p>

<p>Have dependents</p>

<p>Need assistance with basic tax preparation</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Appointment Required:</p>

<p>Tuesdays: 5:00 PM – 8:00 PM</p>

<p>Saturdays: 9:00 AM – 4:00 PM</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Location:
<br />Howard University (details provided when appointment is scheduled)</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Contact / Appointments:
<br />📞 202-838-7798
<br />📧 <a href="mailto:HowardUniversityVITA@gmail.com">HowardUniversityVITA@gmail.com</a></p>

<p> </p>

<p>Important Notes (Scope of Service):
<br />Tax services are free for returns within the scope of volunteer training and certification. Out-of-scope returns include, but are not limited to:</p>

<p>Virtual currency transactions</p>

<p>Complex investment income or stock trades</p>

<p>Rental income or income from selling goods</p>

<p>Business income with paid helpers, losses, or home office use</p>

<p>Income from overseas or international organizations</p>

<p>Individuals without U.S. citizenship or a green card who arrived during the tax year</p>

<p>Individuals in the U.S. on F, J, A, H, L, or M visas</p>

<p><a href="https://events.howard.edu/event/howard-university-volunteer-income-tax-assistance-program">View on site</a> | <a href="mailto:?subject=I found an interesting event%3A Howard University Volunteer Income Tax Assistance Program &amp;body=I found an interesting event you may like%3A%0A%0A%0ADate%3A Mar 17%2C 2026%0A%0ADescription%3A%0AThe Center for Accounting Education%E2%80%99s Volunteer Income Tax Assistance %28VITA%29 Program provides free basic tax preparation services by IRS-trained volunteer tax preparers. Services are available to eligible Washington%2C DC%E2%80%93area residents and Howard University students.%0A%0A %0A%0AEligibility%3A%0AServices are available to individuals who%3A%0A%0AEarn %2469%2C000 or less %28low to moderate or fixed income%29%0A%0AAre elderly or disabled%0A%0AHave dependents%0A%0ANeed assistance with basic tax preparation%0A%0A %0A%0AAppointment Required%3A%0A%0ATuesdays%3A 5%3A00 PM %E2%80%93 8%3A00 PM%0A%0ASaturdays%3A 9%3A00 AM %E2%80%93 4%3A00 PM%0A%0A %0A%0ALocation%3A%0AHoward University %28details provided when appointment is scheduled%29%0A%0A %0A%0AContact %2F Appointments%3A%0A%F0%9F%93%9E 202-838-7798%0A%F0%9F%93%A7 HowardUniversityVITA%40gmail.com%0A%0A %0A%0AImportant Notes %28Scope of Service%29%3A%0ATax services are free for returns within the scope of volunteer training and certification. Out-of-scope returns include%2C but are not limited to%3A%0A%0AVirtual currency transactions%0A%0AComplex investment income or stock trades%0A%0ARental income or income from selling goods%0A%0ABusiness income with paid helpers%2C losses%2C or home office use%0A%0AIncome from overseas or international organizations%0A%0AIndividuals without U.S. citizenship or a green card who arrived during the tax year%0A%0AIndividuals in the U.S. on F%2C J%2C A%2C H%2C L%2C or M visas%0A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fevents.howard.edu%2Fevent%2Fhoward-university-volunteer-income-tax-assistance-program%0A">Email this event</a></p></div></div>]]></descriptio