    <item>
      <title>Black Press Day 2026 at Blackburn Center (Armour J. Blackburn University Center)</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/51948742438929/huge/39d70129c552d02dbdd4dfaf690430de2e16cd57.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Wed, 18 Mar 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>The Moorland–Spingarn Research Center (MSRC) and the National Newspaper Publishers Association (NNPA) invite the Howard University community, the Washington, DC community, and local and national stakeholders to join us for Black Press Day 2026 on Wednesday, March 18, 2026 from 10AM-1PM, at Howard University in the Blackburn Center. Black Press Day is a national convening that honors the legacy, impact, and future of the Black press, highlighting its enduring role in truth-telling, advocacy, and community empowerment. This gathering will celebrate the vital contributions of Black-owned media while fostering dialogue about the press’s continued role in advancing equity and informing our communities.</p>

<p><a href="https://events.howard.edu/event/black-press-day-2026">View on site</a> | <a href="mailto:?subject=I found an interesting event%3A Black Press Day 2026&amp;body=I found an interesting event you may like%3A%0A%0A%0ADate%3A Mar 18%2C 2026%0A%0ADescription%3A%0AThe Moorland%E2%80%93Spingarn Research Center %28MSRC%29 and the National Newspaper Publishers Association %28NNPA%29 invite the Howard University community%2C the Washington%2C DC community%2C and local and national stakeholders to join us for Black Press Day 2026 on Wednesday%2C March 18%2C 2026 from 10AM-1PM%2C at Howard University in the Blackburn Center. Black Press Day is a national convening that honors the legacy%2C impact%2C and future of the Black press%2C highlighting its enduring role in truth-telling%2C advocacy%2C and community empowerment. This gathering will celebrate the vital contributions of Black-owned media while fostering dialogue about the press%E2%80%99s continued role in advancing equity and informing our communities.%0A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fevents.howard.edu%2Fevent%2Fblack-press-day-2026%0A">Email this event</a></p></div></div>]]></description>
